HEADWORD: Roasting
<hw>Roast"ing</hw>, <def><pos>a. & n.</pos>, from <er>Roast</er>,
<pos>v.</pos></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Roasting ear</b></col>, <cd>an ear of Indian corn at that
stage of development when it is fit to be eaten roasted.</cd> --
<col><b>Roasting jack</b></col>, <cd>a machine for turning a spit on
which meat is roasted.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

